SOQL for loops

This is a governor-limit and heap-safety feature, not just syntactic sugar. Two forms:
apex// Single-record form (rarely what you want)
for (Account a : [SELECT Id, Name FROM Account WHERE Industry = 'Tech']) {
    // a is one Account per iteration
}

// Batched form — processes 200 records per chunk
for (List<Account> batch : [SELECT Id, Name FROM Account]) {
    for (Account a : batch) { /* ... */ }
    // update batch;   // DML on 200 at a time
}
The reason this matters: a SOQL for loop streams results in batches of 200 rather than materializing the entire result set in the heap at once. 
If you queried a million rows into a List<Account>, you'd blow the 6 MB heap limit; the for loop form keeps only 200 in memory per iteration. 
So for large data volumes, prefer the for loop over assigning to a List variable. (Note it doesn't raise the 50,000-row total query limit — that still applies — it just controls heap.) 
