Dynamic SOQL

When the query string isn't known until runtime (user-selected filters, a configurable object name), build it as a String and run it with Database.query():
apexString objName = 'Account';
String field   = 'Industry';
String value   = 'Technology';

String q = 'SELECT Id, Name FROM ' + objName + ' WHERE ' + field + ' = :value';
List<sObject> rows = Database.query(q);   // bind vars in scope still work!
Two things to internalize here. First, bind variables still work in dynamic SOQL — :value resolves against your Apex scope — so use them and never concatenate user input directly. 
Second, when you must concatenate a string into the query (like a LIKE search term), wrap it in String.escapeSingleQuotes() to prevent SOQL injection:
apexString userInput = getSearchTerm();
String safe = String.escapeSingleQuotes(userInput);
String q = 'SELECT Id FROM Contact WHERE LastName LIKE \'%' + safe + '%\'';
Database.query() returns a single list; Database.getQueryLocator() is the variant you pass to Batch Apex. 
There's also Database.queryWithBinds() (newer) that takes an explicit bind map instead of relying on scope.
